	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64677682"><p><div class="quote"><p>By making it phone home, it's a much easier way to ensure people have paid [...] However, once a company is no longer willing to support the servers that make the game playable, they should definitely be required to release a patch that makes the game playable without phoning home.</p></div><p>But then I have to trust that will happen, which I don't.</p><p>Hence I don't buy SP games with online requirements.</p><p>If the developers want my money, they will make the game playable without asking them for permission on launch.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64677682">

</div>
