	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64677400"><p>I've never been into gaming, so it had never occurred to me before now that it's part of our cultural heritage. Totally aside from the "I paid for it so I should be able to continue playing" issue, letting games lapse is the equivalent of burying or burning books when their copyright period expires.</p><p>Any creative endeavour should continue to be available for as long as it's of even historical interest. When a company decides to no longer support a game, it should be legally obligated to release all of the source code, protocols, artwork, etc to the public domain.</p></div>
	</div>

